A BILL ENTITLED
1 AN ACT concerning
2 Departments of Public Works – Water Main Breaks – Publication Requirement
3 FOR the purpose of requiring the Department of Public Works for each county in which a
4 water main breaks or leaks to publish certain information on the department’s
5 website; requiring each department to update certain information within a certain
6 time frame; and generally relating to water main breaks and leaks.
7 BY adding to
8 Article – Local Government
9 Section 1–1321
10 Annotated Code of Maryland
11 (2013 Volume and 2024 Supplement)
12 SECTION 1. BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF MARYLAND,
13 That the Laws of Maryland read as follows:
14 Article – Local Government
15 1–1321.
16 (A) THE DEPARTMENT OF PUBLIC WORKS FOR EACH COUNTY IN WHICH A
17 WATER MAIN BREAK OR LEAK OCCURS SHALL PUBLISH ON THE DEPARTMENT’S
18 WEBSITE THE FOLLOWING INFORMATION:
19 (1) THE DATE THE DEPARTMENT WAS NOTIFIED OF THE BREAK OR
20 LEAK;
21 (2) THE DATE OF COMPLIANCE WITH ANY LEGAL AND REGULATORY
22 REQUIREMENTS BY THE RELEVANT WATER UTILITY;
